WEBVTT

00:00.267 --> 00:01.533
ADULT ADAM:
<i> Back in the '80s,</i>

00:01.535 --> 00:03.002
<i> my best friend</i>
<i> was my grandfather.</i>

00:03.004 --> 00:04.336
<i> If there was something</i>
<i> awesome to do,</i>

00:04.338 --> 00:05.871
<i> I was gonna tackle it</i>
<i> with Pops,</i>

00:05.873 --> 00:07.873
<i> and that week,</i>
<i> that awesome thing would be</i>

00:07.875 --> 00:11.276
<i> the most hyped movie</i>
<i> of our time...</i> Batman.

00:11.278 --> 00:11.677
Pops...
Oh.

00:11.679 --> 00:14.613
I have the biggest news
in your 80-some years of life.

00:14.615 --> 00:18.851
A Batman movie's coming out,
and it's going to be awesome!

00:18.853 --> 00:19.852
Batm'n? I'm in!

00:19.854 --> 00:23.555
Me and your dad
loved the old
Adam West TV show.

00:23.557 --> 00:24.023
Didn't we, Murray?

00:24.025 --> 00:26.525
(IMITATES ADAM WEST)
It appears to me,
Commissioner Gordon,

00:26.527 --> 00:31.797
that the Joker, Riddler,
and the Catwoman
have escaped.

00:31.799 --> 00:33.198
What is that?
What is he doing?

00:33.200 --> 00:34.666
I think that's Adam West
as Batm'n.

00:34.668 --> 00:41.340
Your inability to identify
this spot-on impression
is criminal.

00:41.342 --> 00:44.209
Come on. Let's go see
Adam West on the big screen

00:44.211 --> 00:45.978
before your dad
ruins it forever!

00:45.980 --> 00:48.080
Actually, the new movie
stars Michael Keaton.

00:48.082 --> 00:50.682
The guy who plays
Beetle-Buzz?
Beetlejuice.

00:50.684 --> 00:52.251
Beetle-Jazz
can't be Batm'n.

00:52.253 --> 00:56.255
There is only one
Caped Crusader,
and that is me.

00:56.257 --> 00:58.624
Stop it!
Why is he doing
that weird voice?

00:58.626 --> 00:59.992
'Cause we're going
to see<i> Batman.</i>

00:59.994 --> 01:01.727
I've been waiting
to see that for months!

01:01.729 --> 01:04.830
I'm gonna grab my coat
and pound a couple of Jolts.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.031
I wanna make sure
I'm really wired

01:06.033 --> 01:08.033
when I yell things
back at the screen.

01:08.035 --> 01:10.669
It appears the Batcave
is all mine

01:10.671 --> 01:15.407
to watch the Bat-Television
in my Bat-Underpants.

01:15.409 --> 01:17.042
Stop it!
Come on. Let's go.

01:17.044 --> 01:20.245
To the Batmobile!
To the Bat-Recliner.

01:20.748 --> 01:21.947
Ah!

01:22.516 --> 01:23.849
Oh, man.
This is awesome.

01:23.851 --> 01:27.352
Great movie,
great seats, great snacks.

01:27.354 --> 01:29.521
Doesn't get any better
than this.

01:30.424 --> 01:32.057
Is that seat taken?

01:32.059 --> 01:33.225
Is that seat taken?

01:33.227 --> 01:34.226
(GROANS) Okay.

01:34.228 --> 01:35.894
Oh, no, it's Barry!

01:35.896 --> 01:36.662
Is that seat taken?

01:36.664 --> 01:39.198
We invited Barry
and forgot all about him.

01:39.200 --> 01:41.500
Technically,
he invited himself...
Is that seat taken?

01:41.502 --> 01:42.201
...so I feel no remorse.

01:42.203 --> 01:44.937
Yo! Can you
move your wheelchair
so I can sit there?

01:44.939 --> 01:48.640
Come on.
He's your brother.
We got to say sorry.

01:48.642 --> 01:49.775
Is that seat taken?
Do we?

01:49.777 --> 01:52.744
Is that seat taken?
I mean, everything
is so perfect right now.

01:52.746 --> 01:54.379
That seat taken?
That seat's taken, too.

01:54.381 --> 01:58.083
It's just one little "sorry."
He'll understand.

01:58.085 --> 01:59.251
What the hell?

01:59.253 --> 02:02.621
You guys ditched me,
now I'm walking around
like a schmuck,

02:02.623 --> 02:03.555
begging strangers
to move over?

02:03.557 --> 02:06.892
We were just so excited
to see the movie.
You get it.

02:06.894 --> 02:07.726
I don't get it!

02:07.728 --> 02:10.796
Where's my seat?
I think there's a couple
seats in the front row.

02:10.798 --> 02:13.565
So you expect me
to sit alone
in the front row,

02:13.567 --> 02:16.602
craning my neck up
at the giant screen
like putz-bag?

02:16.604 --> 02:17.936
You don't have to do it
like a putz-bag.

02:17.938 --> 02:22.508
No way.
It's only fair if we all sit
in the terrible front row.

02:22.510 --> 02:23.842
Pfft. How is that fair?

02:23.844 --> 02:26.445
Two words... Family.

02:29.283 --> 02:31.750
Okay, look,
the movie's about to start.

02:31.752 --> 02:35.787
Just sit up there, and...
And we'll meet up afterwards.

02:35.789 --> 02:36.054
Fine!

02:36.056 --> 02:39.558
But this is the worst thing
that anyone has ever
done to me.

02:41.362 --> 02:42.561
<i> ¶ I'm twisted up inside</i>

02:42.563 --> 02:46.999
<i> ¶ But nonetheless</i>
<i> I feel the need to say</i>

02:48.869 --> 02:49.768
<i> ¶ I don't know the future</i>

02:49.770 --> 02:53.372
<i> ¶ But the past keeps getting</i>
<i> clearer every day ¶</i>

02:53.374 --> 02:55.507
ADULT ADAM:<i> It was April 5th,</i>
<i> 1980-something.</i>

02:55.509 --> 02:58.277
<i> My sister's senior year</i>
<i> was cruising right along,</i>

02:58.279 --> 02:59.411
<i> until this happened.</i>

02:59.413 --> 03:00.879
Question...
What is this garbage?

03:00.881 --> 03:04.516
Oh, goodie! You got
your college interview
for Penn State!

03:04.518 --> 03:06.351
Thing is,
I didn't schedule it,

03:06.353 --> 03:06.818
and I'm not going.

03:06.820 --> 03:09.254
Carnegie Mellon is
the only school I care about.

03:09.256 --> 03:10.789
Well, you always
need a backup.

03:10.791 --> 03:12.491
That's why I always
bake two pies,

03:12.493 --> 03:14.993
in case Murray eats one
while sleepwalking.

03:14.995 --> 03:16.562
Mom, if I don't get into CMU,

03:16.564 --> 03:17.629
then I'm just gonna
skip college

03:17.631 --> 03:19.364
to busk on the street
like a true artist.

03:19.366 --> 03:21.200
So, what am I supposed
to tell people?

03:21.202 --> 03:24.036
"Oh, there's my daughter,
singing next to a hobo

03:24.038 --> 03:26.038
"who's going pishy
on another hobo."

03:26.040 --> 03:27.940
Penn State is amazing!

03:27.942 --> 03:31.376
That place made your father
everything he is today.

03:31.378 --> 03:32.544
Bevy.

03:32.546 --> 03:33.812
I lost another hot dog.

03:33.814 --> 03:35.547
What? Why does this
keep happening?

03:35.549 --> 03:37.749
I guess 'cause my, uh,
gesturing hand

03:37.751 --> 03:39.484
is also my
hot-dog-holding hand.

03:39.486 --> 03:41.286
I think my point here
is proven.

03:41.288 --> 03:42.321
Murray, your daughter thinks

03:42.323 --> 03:44.957
she's too good to go
to her Penn State interview.

03:44.959 --> 03:47.593
Let's get something straight,
little missy.

03:47.595 --> 03:48.727
Graduating from Penn State

03:48.729 --> 03:51.330
is the greatest accomplishment
of my life.

03:51.332 --> 03:53.599
Too bad, Dad. I'm going
to Carnegie Mellon.

03:53.601 --> 03:55.000
You are going
to Penn State.

03:55.002 --> 03:57.803
It is cheaper,
it's more affordable,

03:57.805 --> 03:58.604
and it costs less!

03:58.606 --> 04:00.439
That's the same thing
said three different ways!

04:00.441 --> 04:04.343
Well, if it's
good enough for me,
it's good enough for you.

04:04.345 --> 04:05.277
Okay, fine.

04:05.279 --> 04:06.211
I guess I didn't realize

04:06.213 --> 04:07.746
how important
this was to you.

04:07.748 --> 04:08.647
I promise to take

04:08.649 --> 04:10.349
my Penn State
interview seriously.

04:10.351 --> 04:11.850
ADULT ADAM:<i> By "seriously",</i>
<i> my sister meant</i>

04:11.852 --> 04:14.152
<i> "intentionally tank"</i>
<i> her Penn State interview.</i>

04:14.154 --> 04:16.121
Yo, dude!
Sorry I'm two hours late.

04:16.123 --> 04:17.889
Uh, well, three.
(CHUCKLES)

04:17.891 --> 04:19.858
No worries.
Come on in!

04:20.361 --> 04:22.794
Oh! Two points!

04:22.796 --> 04:23.762
Oh! Wow.

04:23.764 --> 04:26.198
There's not even a trash can
there. (CHUCKLES)

04:26.200 --> 04:27.099
Have a seat. (CLEARS THROAT)

04:27.101 --> 04:30.335
I'm Kyle Schnitz, and it is
very nice to meet you.

04:30.337 --> 04:31.436
My favorite part
of being an alum

04:31.438 --> 04:35.574
is getting to interview
all kinds of great students.

04:35.576 --> 04:36.541
Oh, full disclosure.

04:36.543 --> 04:38.644
I'm not so much a, uh,
great student

04:38.646 --> 04:40.345
as I am a cheater.
I'm sorry.

04:40.347 --> 04:42.014
Aw! That's a cute dog
you got there.

04:42.016 --> 04:45.450
Oh. Uh, thank you.
Yes, that's Ruffles.
He's a rescue.

04:45.452 --> 04:46.852
No, I'm talking
about your wife.

04:46.854 --> 04:49.688
Boom! Upstairs!
(CHUCKLES)

04:50.157 --> 04:52.491
Just gonna leave me
hanging like that?

04:52.493 --> 04:53.025
Lame.

04:53.027 --> 04:55.927
Let's just forge onward,
shall we? Um, so...

04:55.929 --> 04:59.131
What programs at Penn State
are you most excited to...

04:59.133 --> 05:00.799
Oh, my!
What are you doing?

05:00.801 --> 05:03.568
(MUFFLED) Taking on this
meatball sub like a champ.

05:03.570 --> 05:05.070
Want some, Kenny?
It's... Kyle.

05:05.072 --> 05:08.040
Uh, would you please
not get sauce all over my...

05:08.042 --> 05:09.708
Gah! Damn it!
That's my name placard!

05:09.710 --> 05:12.778
All right. Let me, uh,
cut to the chase here, Kyle.

05:12.780 --> 05:16.181
I am one hell of a singer.
I mean, check out these pipes.

05:16.183 --> 05:17.449
(CLEARS THROAT)

05:17.451 --> 05:21.753
<i> ¶ Kyle Schnitz</i>
<i> smells like farts</i>

05:21.755 --> 05:25.390
<i> ¶ Oh, stinky, stinky farts ¶</i>

05:25.392 --> 05:27.159
That was right off
the top of the dome.

05:27.161 --> 05:27.959
And interview over!

05:27.961 --> 05:29.461
ADULT ADAM:<i> The only thing</i>
<i> more uncomfortable</i>

05:29.463 --> 05:33.065
<i> than Erica's interview</i>
<i> was Barry's seat at the movie.</i>

05:35.469 --> 05:36.935
<i> Wait till they get</i>
<i> a load of me.</i>

05:36.937 --> 05:40.872
What's happening?
This isn't like
the TV show at all.

05:40.874 --> 05:42.541
I know!
It's so awesome!

05:42.543 --> 05:44.009
ADULT ADAM:
<i> He certainly was to me.</i>

05:44.011 --> 05:47.579
<i> But to Pops, his Batman</i>
<i> was from the old TV show.</i>

05:47.581 --> 05:48.080
This is crazy.

05:48.082 --> 05:51.083
You really think Adam West
is the better Batman?

05:51.085 --> 05:51.850
He's the only Batm'n.

05:51.852 --> 05:55.620
And this new fancy movie
forgot the best part!

05:55.622 --> 05:59.925
Where were the
"POWs" and "BAMs"
when Batm'n socks the Joker?

05:59.927 --> 06:03.028
I'm not so sure
you need to see
big cartoon words

06:03.030 --> 06:04.162
when Bat punches a dude.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.297
We'll just watch
the old show,

06:05.299 --> 06:07.065
and then you'll see
what I'm talking about.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.633
Well, no matter
which Batman is better,

06:08.635 --> 06:11.670
at least we can agree
we had an awesome day
together.

06:12.840 --> 06:13.939
(CLATTERING)

06:13.941 --> 06:17.843
What the hell?

06:17.845 --> 06:18.877
Oh, no.
Balls.

06:18.879 --> 06:19.878
Balls is right, man!

06:19.880 --> 06:22.914
Who exactly are you
talking to right now?
You!

06:22.916 --> 06:25.350
My neck is just jacked up
from sitting in the front row.

06:25.352 --> 06:28.954
We were bickering
about Batm'n,
and forgot you were up there.

06:28.956 --> 06:32.791
But this always happens!
You two do everything
without me!

06:32.793 --> 06:34.292
Well, I know
this looks bad,

06:34.294 --> 06:37.262
but we never leave you
out of the fun!

06:37.264 --> 06:38.430
(OVEN TIMER DINGS)
What was that?

06:38.432 --> 06:39.698
Nothing.
What's in the oven, dudes?

06:39.700 --> 06:41.466
Don't look in the oven,
Barry.
You better not be doing

06:41.468 --> 06:43.301
what I think you're doing.
Don't look in the oven!

06:43.303 --> 06:47.439
I'm going to the oven!
I'm looking inside!

06:47.908 --> 06:50.609
Oh, my God!

06:50.878 --> 06:55.113
You two made
Batman Shrinky Dinks...

06:55.215 --> 06:56.381
Without me?

06:56.383 --> 06:59.785
You know I live
for shrinking dinks.

06:59.787 --> 07:01.720
We know that.
Everyone knows that!

07:01.722 --> 07:04.589
There's only two
shrunken dinks, man!

07:04.591 --> 07:06.591
Not three dinks.
Just two!

07:06.593 --> 07:10.829
Yeah, 'cause it's
one dink for me
and one dink for you.

07:10.831 --> 07:14.132
Don't! Just don't.

07:14.134 --> 07:15.267
(OVEN DOOR CLOSES)

07:15.269 --> 07:17.269
You're gonna pay for this.

07:17.271 --> 07:19.771
Oh, Barry, come back.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.306
You can have my dink.

07:21.308 --> 07:24.643
You can have my dink,
Barry!

07:24.645 --> 07:25.444
BEVERLY: Murray!

07:25.446 --> 07:27.813
Your daughter has
some huge news!

07:27.815 --> 07:29.648
Erica, tell your father
all about...

07:29.650 --> 07:31.249
Okay, I can't
stand it anymore!

07:31.251 --> 07:34.085
She said she killed
in her interview... Killed!

07:34.087 --> 07:35.353
Whoo-hoo!
That's my peanut!

07:35.355 --> 07:38.356
Yep! I really
made an impression
on the Penn State guy.

07:38.358 --> 07:40.225
Like, he's never
gonna forget me.

07:40.227 --> 07:43.462
(LAUGHING) Oh, my God.
I'm so happy, I could (BLEEP)

07:43.464 --> 07:45.297
That's actually, uh,
good timing,

07:45.299 --> 07:49.234
'cause Carnegie Mellon
just sent you a letter,

07:49.236 --> 07:50.702
and it's kind of thin.

07:50.704 --> 07:52.103
Oh, no! It is thin!

07:52.105 --> 07:54.706
If they said yes,
they wouldn't send
the thin one!

07:54.708 --> 07:56.475
Wait. Maybe they, uh,
just sent a pre-letter

07:56.477 --> 07:59.110
to tell me that
the thick one's
on the way, and...

07:59.112 --> 08:01.046
Son of a bitch!

08:01.048 --> 08:02.180
I got rejected!

08:02.182 --> 08:04.316
Carnegie Mellon
rejected my baby?

08:04.318 --> 08:06.651
(SCOFFS) Well, I'm never
buying another melon!

08:06.653 --> 08:11.056
From this moment on,
this family eats
tree fruits only.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.757
No more scoopable fruits.
You hear me?

08:12.759 --> 08:15.160
Good news, though.
You got your backup.

08:15.162 --> 08:18.930
Yes! That is good news,
that I have a backup.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.533
Murray's an alum,
and you will be, too.

08:21.535 --> 08:23.268
Penn State is happening.

08:23.270 --> 08:24.936
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:24.938 --> 08:28.206
Well, um...
I have to go for, uh...

08:28.208 --> 08:30.475
For a reason
I can't think of right now,

08:30.477 --> 08:32.644
but it's real, so bye.

08:34.348 --> 08:36.414
Hey!
Oh, no! She's back.

08:36.416 --> 08:39.518
It's okay! It's me,
Erica Goldberg.

08:39.520 --> 08:40.886
Uh, yeah. I remember.

08:40.888 --> 08:45.657
I'm going to my car now,
and my secretary knows
I'm down here.

08:45.659 --> 08:48.393
Wait. No. Don't
walk away from me.

08:48.762 --> 08:49.461
Or run!

08:49.463 --> 08:50.662
Don't make me
chase you, Schnitz!

08:50.664 --> 08:52.631
Oh, God. My secretary
has no idea where I am.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.132
I slipped out to go
to my pottery class!

08:54.134 --> 08:56.735
Look, I know
I messed up my interview,

08:56.737 --> 08:57.569
but I have my reasons!

08:57.571 --> 08:59.671
I only tanked it
on purpose out of spite!

08:59.673 --> 09:01.473
That's even worse
than being crazy.

09:01.475 --> 09:02.974
I'm not crazy,
and this proves it!

09:02.976 --> 09:05.243
Look at my teacher
recommendations!
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

09:05.245 --> 09:07.445
Just look at them!
Damn it!

09:07.447 --> 09:09.915
You are nuts, lady!
And I have good SATs! Ow!

09:09.917 --> 09:12.450
I need to get a will.
And I played soccer
in the 10th grade!

09:12.452 --> 09:16.254
I was also
Model U.N. Treasurer!
(TIRES SQUEAL)

09:18.825 --> 09:19.324
I think that helped.

09:19.326 --> 09:22.360
ADULT ADAM:<i> With that,</i>
<i> Erica officially lost</i>
<i> her backup school.</i>

09:22.362 --> 09:24.629
<i> Meanwhile, Pops was</i>
<i> giving me an education</i>

09:24.631 --> 09:26.498
<i> on the old version</i>
<i> of</i> Batman.

09:26.500 --> 09:28.767
See that?
It's a camera trick.

09:28.769 --> 09:32.037
Th... They shoot it sideways.
Yeah, I got it.

09:32.039 --> 09:33.705
Now, this is Batm'n!

09:33.707 --> 09:34.739
ADULT ADAM:<i> Little did I know,</i>

09:34.741 --> 09:36.641
<i> my scorned brother</i>
<i> was lurking in the shadows</i>

09:36.643 --> 09:39.044
<i> and planning a dastardly</i>
<i> revenge plot to ensure</i>

09:39.046 --> 09:42.514
<i> that me and my grandfather</i>
<i> would never forget him again.</i>

09:42.516 --> 09:44.382
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

09:44.384 --> 09:45.850
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

09:46.787 --> 09:48.019
What?

09:48.021 --> 09:49.454
ADULT ADAM:
<i> Like the Joker himself,</i>

09:49.456 --> 09:50.322
<i> Barry set a treacherous trap</i>

09:50.324 --> 09:52.791
<i> that would destroy</i>
<i> the dynamic duo forever.</i>

09:52.793 --> 09:55.994
Adam! Come quick!
It's an emergency!

09:57.431 --> 09:59.264
Oh! Thanks
for dropping by.

09:59.266 --> 10:00.732
You said
it was an emergency.

10:00.734 --> 10:02.767
A hang-with-my-bro
emergency.

10:02.769 --> 10:04.669
Here, have a seat.

10:05.172 --> 10:06.371
No!

10:06.940 --> 10:08.440
This chair.

10:09.876 --> 10:12.177
And action...

10:12.179 --> 10:13.511
Is my favorite
movie genre.

10:13.513 --> 10:18.483
Which reminds me,
I saw you watching that
old<i> Batman</i> TV show.

10:18.485 --> 10:19.517
Pops was right.

10:19.519 --> 10:21.119
Adam West is better
than Keaton.

10:21.121 --> 10:23.655
Pops doesn't know
the first thing
about<i> Batman.</i>

10:23.657 --> 10:26.625
He doesn't even say it right.
He says "Batm'n."

10:26.627 --> 10:28.893
But you told Pops
you love his show.

10:28.895 --> 10:30.829
It kind of sounds like
you lied to his face.

10:30.831 --> 10:34.165
I had to. It's just...
It's so corny!

10:34.167 --> 10:34.966
Say it louder.

10:34.968 --> 10:36.601
I mean,
it made no sense at all.

10:36.603 --> 10:38.069
They had a bat-calendar.

10:38.071 --> 10:40.205
Move more into the light.
And bat shark repellant?

10:40.207 --> 10:44.242
Why would a superhero
even have that
on his utility belt? Why?

10:44.244 --> 10:46.878
So you don't just
reject Pops' Batman.

10:46.880 --> 10:49.514
You reject Pops
as a human old person?

10:49.516 --> 10:50.782
Nah, I'm just humoring him.

10:50.784 --> 10:54.419
All that old-timey stuff he
likes, it's just not for me.

10:54.421 --> 10:55.120
And cut.

10:55.122 --> 10:56.821
Why would you say that?
No reason.

10:56.823 --> 10:57.822
I always like our talks.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.524
Go away now.
Come on. Come on.

10:59.526 --> 11:01.660
ADULT ADAM:
<i> And with that, my brother</i>
<i> had everything he needed</i>

11:01.662 --> 11:06.564
<i> to become a villain</i>
<i> that could even rival</i>
<i> Jack Nicholson's Joker.</i>

11:06.800 --> 11:08.099
Wait till they
get a load of me.

11:08.101 --> 11:11.269
What'd you say?
Nothing! Go away now!

11:12.939 --> 11:14.706
Wait till they
get a load of...

11:14.708 --> 11:18.209
Nope. Moment's passed.
Damn it.

11:19.613 --> 11:22.881
ADULT ADAM:
<i> It had been a day since my</i>
<i> sister's Penn State disaster,</i>

11:22.883 --> 11:26.384
<i> and our parents still</i>
<i> didn't know until now.</i>

11:26.386 --> 11:27.719
Hey, folks,
no need for alarm,

11:27.721 --> 11:30.388
except for the incredibly
alarming phone call
I just got.

11:30.390 --> 11:33.391
It seems that Erica tanked
her interview with Penn State,

11:33.393 --> 11:36.227
and then attacked the man
in a parking garage.

11:36.229 --> 11:38.163
What?
What have you done,
child?

11:38.165 --> 11:38.930
It's not my fault!

11:38.932 --> 11:40.665
Dad said I had to go
to Penn State,

11:40.667 --> 11:42.667
and I wanted CMU,
and now I have nothing,

11:42.669 --> 11:45.036
and, dear Lord,
this is a disaster!

11:45.038 --> 11:46.237
Look, you folks can relax

11:46.239 --> 11:49.174
because ol' Glascott
has the solution.

11:49.176 --> 11:50.375
Good.
Thank God.

11:50.377 --> 11:51.042
I have failed
as a mother.

11:51.044 --> 11:55.180
Are any of you familiar
with the International
Correspondence School?

11:55.182 --> 11:58.049
<i> Do you want to</i>
<i> make more money?</i>
<i> Sure, we all do.</i>

11:58.051 --> 12:00.118
You may have seen
their catchy TV commercials

12:00.120 --> 12:03.021
starring America's sweetheart,
Sally Struthers.

12:03.023 --> 12:04.322
Don't.
Ooh, look!

12:04.324 --> 12:05.123
In just two short years,

12:05.125 --> 12:07.358
you can get a degree
in TV/VCR repair.

12:07.360 --> 12:08.626
But I don't want to fix TVs!

12:08.628 --> 12:10.929
Well, luckily, you have
a bunch of other options...

12:10.931 --> 12:13.364
Gun repair, child daycare,

12:13.366 --> 12:15.133
learning the personal
computer.

12:15.135 --> 12:17.435
