read it out loud!

12:19.039 --> 12:20.872
Interior decorating?
Cooking?

12:20.874 --> 12:22.674
Art? Air condition
and maintenance?

12:22.676 --> 12:25.076
I mean, what does this
school not have?

12:25.078 --> 12:26.845
A campus.
This is a nightmare!

12:26.847 --> 12:28.613
Okay, let's all
just take a breath.

12:28.615 --> 12:30.548
We've got one card
left to play.

12:30.550 --> 12:31.816
Murray, you're an alum.

12:31.818 --> 12:34.219
You'll go down there
and straighten this
whole mess out.

12:34.221 --> 12:36.154
Yeah, I don't think
that's a good idea.

12:36.156 --> 12:38.022
What? Why not?
She made her bed,

12:38.024 --> 12:40.158
and now she's gonna
have to lie in it!

12:40.160 --> 12:42.460
Kid's got to learn.
Yeah. In college.

12:42.462 --> 12:44.929
Okay, I am not
getting involved.

12:44.931 --> 12:48.433
End of story!
Do not pry!

12:48.435 --> 12:48.933
Shh!

12:48.935 --> 12:50.468
Well, I am getting you
into Penn State.

12:50.470 --> 12:54.572
No child of mine will deal
with the consequences
of her actions!

12:54.574 --> 12:55.740
Excuse me.

12:55.742 --> 12:56.474
1-800...

12:56.476 --> 12:59.344
ADULT ADAM:
<i> As Erica's college career</i>
<i> went up in flames,</i>

12:59.346 --> 13:01.980
<i> my plan to shoot</i>
<i> a Batman movie with Pops</i>

13:01.982 --> 13:03.414
<i> was about to be shut down.</i>

13:03.416 --> 13:04.949
Well, well, well.

13:04.951 --> 13:07.418
If it isn't Adamander
Goldberg in the flesh.

13:07.420 --> 13:09.487
Adamander?
We need to talk,
my friend.

13:09.489 --> 13:11.856
You think Adam is short
for Adamander?

13:11.858 --> 13:12.757
It's time
to pay the piper.

13:12.759 --> 13:15.460
Do you think
it's like Alexander?
Forget the name!

13:15.462 --> 13:17.262
You got other things
to worry about.

13:17.264 --> 13:17.829
ADULT ADAM:<i> Did I ever.</i>

13:17.831 --> 13:21.833
<i> At that very moment,</i>
<i> Pops would stumble upon</i>
<i> a secret recording of me</i>

13:21.835 --> 13:23.134
<i> bashing him</i>
<i> and all he held dear.</i>

13:23.136 --> 13:24.736
(ON RECORDING)
<i> Nah, I'm just humoring him.</i>

13:24.738 --> 13:27.105
<i> All that old-timey stuff</i>
<i> he likes,</i>

13:27.107 --> 13:28.339
<i> it's just not for me.</i>

13:28.341 --> 13:30.141
Oh, no.
I said awful things

13:30.143 --> 13:32.377
about his terrible version
of<i> Batman.</i>

13:32.379 --> 13:33.945
Yes you did.

13:33.947 --> 13:38.750
For once, Pops is gonna be
in my stupid home movie.

13:38.752 --> 13:40.985
"Rad:
The Barry Goldberg Story."

13:40.987 --> 13:45.523
No! You can't put that
wonderful elderly man
in a BMX movie!

13:45.525 --> 13:48.359
I don't think
you'll be stopping me.

13:51.031 --> 13:53.464
No!
You can't do this!

13:53.466 --> 13:54.899
Okay.
This isn't a problem.

13:54.901 --> 13:56.367
I'll just grab
my toolbox and...

13:56.369 --> 13:59.037
Damn it! I don't have
real-world skills.

13:59.039 --> 14:01.840
Or a utility belt
with actual utilities!

14:01.842 --> 14:04.042
Well, well, looks like you
wanted to get into Penn State

14:04.044 --> 14:06.711
a little bit more than you
thought, hmm, Miss Goldberg?

14:06.713 --> 14:10.148
She does, and we are
so, so grateful

14:10.150 --> 14:12.350
that you agreed
to meet with us today,

14:12.352 --> 14:14.986
and Erica is very sorry
for her behavior.

14:14.988 --> 14:18.423
I really am. I mean,
stalking you in the garage

14:18.425 --> 14:21.526
and singing a hurtful song
about you smelling like poots

14:21.528 --> 14:25.897
and comparing
your wife's appearance
to that of a canine...

14:25.899 --> 14:28.166
It's all very...

14:28.468 --> 14:28.867
Not good.

14:28.869 --> 14:31.502
I might also add,
she ate a sandwich on my desk.

14:31.504 --> 14:34.072
Which reminds me, you know,
I never had my lunch.

14:34.074 --> 14:37.442
Would you mind if I
rudely devoured this
and wasted your time?

14:37.444 --> 14:39.177
Okay, I deserve that.

14:40.714 --> 14:41.746
Mmm, that is very messy.

14:41.748 --> 14:43.314
All right, well,
I made my point, okay?

14:43.316 --> 14:45.350
Well, it might
interest you to know

14:45.352 --> 14:47.151
that my husband,
Murray Goldberg,

14:47.153 --> 14:50.655
is an active alum
of this school.

14:50.657 --> 14:52.156
An active alum?

14:52.158 --> 14:52.991
Active.
Damn it. Fine.

14:52.993 --> 14:56.794
Well, I'm sure we can, uh,
work something out. (CHUCKLES)

14:56.796 --> 14:58.630
Just take a look.

14:58.632 --> 15:01.833
Huh. It appears that
Mr. Goldberg is not,

15:01.835 --> 15:04.369
in fact, a graduate
of Penn State.

15:04.371 --> 15:06.104
What? How dare you!

15:06.106 --> 15:07.605
Oh, see for yourself.

15:07.607 --> 15:12.076
He's one credit shy
of graduation.

15:12.746 --> 15:15.280
I say I'd earned
a celebratory bite, hmm?

15:15.282 --> 15:16.281
(CHUCKLES)

15:16.283 --> 15:20.318
(GROANS) Oh, Schnitz!
I messed myself.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.519
I messed myself.

15:21.521 --> 15:25.657
College dropout?
I'm married to
a college dropout?

15:25.659 --> 15:26.925
You're a college dropout!

15:26.927 --> 15:29.594
I dropped out to marry you,
dropout!

15:29.596 --> 15:30.862
So this is why
you wouldn't help,

15:30.864 --> 15:32.830
because you've been lying
for three decades?

15:32.832 --> 15:36.100
I feel bad, and I say that
from the bottom of my heart

15:36.102 --> 15:38.603
and also to end
this conversation!

15:38.605 --> 15:39.304
This is nuts.

15:39.306 --> 15:41.639
You both lectured me
my entire life

15:41.641 --> 15:42.807
on how important college is,

15:42.809 --> 15:46.277
and now I find out that
neither of you even graduated?

15:46.279 --> 15:47.145
I was one credit short!

15:47.147 --> 15:51.950
You know, if I eat
99% of a sandwich,
I still at a sandwich!

15:51.952 --> 15:54.085
This isn't a sandwich!
It's my future!

15:54.087 --> 15:55.687
Look, it doesn't matter
what I did.

15:55.689 --> 15:56.654
I'm still your father,

15:56.656 --> 15:58.556
and you're not
skipping out on college.

15:58.558 --> 16:01.592
I am done taking life advice
from a hypocrite.

16:01.594 --> 16:03.494
Since none of these colleges
will take me,

16:03.496 --> 16:05.496
I am just gonna focus
on my music

16:05.498 --> 16:09.200
and busk on the streets
like a true artist!

16:09.202 --> 16:11.469
Why didn't you back me up
on the sandwich metaphor?

16:11.471 --> 16:15.039
Well, I hope you're happy.
Your daughter's a busker.

16:15.041 --> 16:17.008
We've lost her
to the streets.

16:17.010 --> 16:17.308
Busking?

16:17.310 --> 16:19.243
ADULT ADAM:
<i> As Erica walked out</i>
<i> on her college future,</i>

16:19.245 --> 16:22.413
<i> Pops had stumbled right into</i>
<i> Barry's supervillain trap,</i>

16:22.415 --> 16:23.014
<i> and it was foolproof.</i>

16:23.016 --> 16:28.052
(SIGHS) Adam said
some pretty nasty words
about everything you love.

16:28.054 --> 16:30.621
Can't imagine what
you must be thinking
right now.

16:30.623 --> 16:32.390
I think you secretly
taped Adam

16:32.392 --> 16:35.727
in a weird attempt to turn us
against each other.

16:35.729 --> 16:37.028
How dare you, sir!

16:37.030 --> 16:39.630
You told Adam
to stand in better light.

16:39.632 --> 16:42.734
You really need to learn
how to grift someone, kiddo.

16:42.736 --> 16:45.870
If anything,
you should be angry at Adam!

16:45.872 --> 16:50.341
He's the one
who bad-mouthed you while
I happened to be filming!

16:50.343 --> 16:51.075
Yeah, where's Adam?

16:51.077 --> 16:53.277
ADULT ADAM:<i> I was trapped</i>
<i> with no way out.</i>

16:53.279 --> 16:54.879
Think, Adamander! Think!

16:54.881 --> 16:56.080
ADULT ADAM:
<i> And then I saw it.</i>

16:56.082 --> 16:58.750
<i> My sheets served</i>
<i> as my own Bat-Signal.</i>

16:58.752 --> 17:00.885
<i> Forget the Batman movie</i>
<i> and TV show.</i>

17:00.887 --> 17:04.889
<i> I'd be the greatest</i>
<i> Dark Knight</i>
<i> Gotham had ever seen!</i>

17:05.191 --> 17:07.725
I told you!
Adam's long gone!

17:07.727 --> 17:09.327
Whoa!
(THUDS)

17:09.429 --> 17:12.363
That looks so much
easier on TV!

17:13.833 --> 17:15.733
Adam, are you okay?
No!

17:15.735 --> 17:17.402
This crazy man
locked me in my room

17:17.404 --> 17:19.470
so he could make
a dirt-biking movie with you!

17:19.472 --> 17:21.372
Barry, why
would you do this?

17:21.374 --> 17:23.041
The kid could have
gotten real hurt.

17:23.043 --> 17:25.076
I just had enough.
Enough of what?

17:25.078 --> 17:27.412
Of you two
leaving me out!

17:27.647 --> 17:30.515
All my life, you guys
have been the dynamic duo...

17:30.517 --> 17:33.918
Having fun,
making awesome movies...

17:33.920 --> 17:37.255
Did it ever occur to you,
just once, maybe
I'd like to be included?

17:37.257 --> 17:41.225
Barry, you're
my grandson, too.
You know I love you.

17:41.227 --> 17:43.461
It doesn't
feel like that, Pops.

17:48.968 --> 17:50.435
ADULT ADAM:<i> With her</i>
<i> college dreams dashed,</i>

17:50.437 --> 17:52.403
<i> Erica would busk her way</i>
<i> to fame and fortune.</i>

17:52.405 --> 17:55.206
<i> Naturally, she'd rely on</i>
<i> the greatest song of the '80s.</i>

17:55.208 --> 17:59.811
<i> ¶ Gonna take a lot</i>
<i> to take me away from you</i>

17:59.813 --> 18:03.314
<i> ¶ There's nothing that</i>
<i> a hundred men or more...</i>

